sub_title: Bachelor of Arts in the Slavonic Languages and Cultures (Russian/Lithuanian comparable Linguistics)
summary:
Bachelor of Arts in Russian Studies/Slavonic languages and culture at Leiden University (Netherlands) with knowlege of English, Dutch, Lithuanian and Russian languages  (French lessons at Secondary school). I'm expierienced in work & travel jobs or seasonal jobs in different countries. I wrote my bachelor thesis about similarities of Russian and Lithuanian comparative linguistics.
Because of my lifestyle I am able to communicate with different people from different countries or cultures and build bridges between them. I see no difference between a simple worker or a director, I look at the personality. Ten years at Ministry of Finance is a perfect environment to meet and get to know different, clever, wel educated people. I have social nature and I like to use it in my life.
